	if ((!current.defect.nil() || (!current.enhancement.nil() || (!current.u_requirement.nil()) || (!current.project.nil())) && current.enhancement.u_enhancement_type == 'ServiceNow')){
		createPracticeStories();

			stask.type = 4;
			stask.state = 1;
			stask.parent = current.sys_id;
			stask.insert();
		}
	}

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_ui_page"><sys_ui_page action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><category>general</category><client_script/><description>UI Page used to request a Standard Change Request from a Task.</description><direct>false</direct><endpoint>x_188354_new_hire_select_training_area.do</endpoint><html><![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<j:jelly trim="false" xmlns:j="jelly:core" xmlns:g="glide" xmlns:j2="null" xmlns:g2="null">
	<g:evaluate var="jvar_getOptions" jelly="true" object="true">
		
		// get hire hire record as current
		var new_hire_sysId = jelly.sysparm_new_hire_sysId;
		var current = new GlideRecord('x_188354_new_hire_training_table');
			current.get(new_hire_sysId);
		
		
		// Get availble training areas
		var query = 'active=true';
		var trainingArea = new GlideRecord('x_188354_new_hire_training_area');

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>false</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>x_188354_new_hire_training_plan</collection><condition/><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition/><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Spin up Modules</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {

	// Add your code here
	
	// Get Modules
	var modulesArr = [];
	var modQuery = 'active=true^training_area='+current.getValue('training_plan');
	var modules = new GlideRecord('x_188354_new_hire_module');
	modules.addEncodedQuery(modQuery);
	modules.query();
	while (modules.next()){
		modulesArr.push({
			'modId':modules.getUniqueValue(),
			'category':modules.category.toString(),
			'sequence':(modules.category.sequence + modules.sequence).toString()
		});
	}
	
	for(var mod in modulesArr){
		var modObj = modulesArr[mod];
		var trainingMod = new GlideRecord('x_188354_new_hire_training_module');
		trainingMod.initialize();
		trainingMod.training_plan = current.getUniqueValue();
		trainingMod.module = modObj.modId;
		trainingMod.status = 'pending';
		trainingMod.category = modObj.category;
		trainingMod.sequence = modObj.sequence;
		trainingMod.available_actions='1dc22833db5a13009927773ebf9619d3';
		trainingMod.insert();
	}
	
	current.status = 'in_progress';
	current.update();

})(current, previous);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-06-01 12:35:02</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>fa4bdcfbdb1a13009927773ebf961929</sys_id><sys_mod_count>5</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Spin up Modules</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="New Hire Training" source="x_188354_new_hire">2c713841db0213009927773ebf96190a</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="New Hire Training">2c713841db0213009927773ebf96190a</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_fa4bdcfbdb1a13009927773ebf961929</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>brent.llewellyn</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-06-01 13:04:26</sys_updated_on><template/><when>after</when></sys_script><sys_translated_text action="delete_multiple" query="documentkey=fa4bdcfbdb1a13009927773ebf961929"/></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: sys_embedded_help_content_1a9845ebdb5213009927773ebf961918
sys_update_xml.payload:
truereportingImport Tables list

This list displays information about external Microsoft Excel data sources that have been imported into your instance. The Import Tables list is visible only to users with admin roles.

Click the column headers to search, sort, filter, and edit data.

The Import Tables list contains the following columns by default:
  • Name – The name given to the data source when the user uploaded it.
  • Table – The name assigned to the table by your instance.
  • Created by user – The user name of the user who uploaded the external file.
  • Filename – The filename of the uploaded Microsoft Excel file.
  • Active – Boolean value. True if the file has not yet expired. The user who uploads the file sets the expiration date.
  • Expiration days – Number of days before the expiration date specified when the file was uploaded.
  • Expire on date – The expiration date specified when the file was uploaded.
  • Expired – Boolean value. True if the expiration date has passed.
Related information
Using imported report data
